---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import LessonNav from "../../components/LessonNav.astro";
import HeroMesh from "../../components/HeroMesh";

const FIPS_REPO = "https://github.com/jmcorgan/fips";
const FIPS_ISSUES = "https://github.com/jmcorgan/fips/issues";
const FIPS_CONTRIBUTING = "https://github.com/jmcorgan/fips/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md";
const FIPS_DESIGN_DOCS = "https://github.com/jmcorgan/fips/tree/master/docs/design";
const FIPS_TESTING = "https://github.com/jmcorgan/fips/tree/master/testing";
const FIPS_SITE = "https://fips.network";
const LEARN_FIPS_REPO = "https://github.com/dergigi/learn-fips";
const CORGAN_QUOTE_URL =
  "https://njump.to/nevent1qqsqjkq3yxynqsj7lkk6dst9h4el8yx4rlwysn8pngqewpxk9aqttncpzamhxue69uhhyetvv9ujumn0wvh8xmmrd9skctczyq4m4nj48mlt7kxa2kgjz60e9sgj86mpy8tm5zf0d3gpqjhuxxkw7qcyqqqqqqgg0hv3z";
const FIPS_ANNOUNCEMENT_URL =
  "https://njump.to/nevent1qvzqqqqqqypzq2a6ee2nal4ltrw4tyfpd8ujcyfradsjr4a6pyhkc5qsft7rrt80qyt8wumn8ghj7cn9wehjumn0wd68yvfwvdhk6tcpz4mhxue69uhhyetvv9ujuerpd46hxtnfduhsqgxxce3t2qj4y3qj30qc6a68hcjkhvuh7ua3ktzu04fqe5gmwhgp8spz62cn";
const FIPS_HASHTAG_URL = "https://ants.sh/t/fips";
const SOVENG_PODCAST_URL =
  "https://sovereignengineering.io/podcast/24-building-fips-w-johnathan-corgan";
---

<Base title="Connect and Contribute">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <p class="text-fips-accent font-mono text-sm mb-2">Lesson 14</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Connect and Contribute</h1>

    <section class="space-y-4 text-fips-text leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        A mesh is only as interesting as the peers on it. FIPS is a young protocol with a small,
        focused group of people working on it. The project grows faster with more nodes, more eyes
        on the specs, and more applications that treat an npub as a first-class address. This page
        is the shortest path from reader to participant.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Where the project lives</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-3 not-prose my-2">
        <a
          href={FIPS_REPO}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30 hover:border-fips-accent/40 transition-colors block"
        >
          <div class="font-semibold text-fips-accent mb-1">jmcorgan/fips</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-fips-muted">
            The reference implementation in Rust. Source, issue tracker, releases.
          </div>
        </a>
        <a
          href={FIPS_DESIGN_DOCS}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30 hover:border-fips-accent/40 transition-colors block"
        >
          <div class="font-semibold text-fips-accent mb-1">docs/design</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-fips-muted">
            The specs this site is built from. Start at <code class="font-mono">fips-intro.md</code
            >.
          </div>
        </a>
        <a
          href={FIPS_SITE}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30 hover:border-fips-accent/40 transition-colors block"
        >
          <div class="font-semibold text-fips-accent mb-1">fips.network</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-fips-muted">
            Project homepage, status, and deployed test mesh.
          </div>
        </a>
        <a
          href={LEARN_FIPS_REPO}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30 hover:border-fips-accent/40 transition-colors block"
        >
          <div class="font-semibold text-fips-accent mb-1">dergigi/learn-fips</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-fips-muted">
            The source of this site. Typos, unclear diagrams, missing lessons all live here.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Reach people directly</h2>

      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-fips-text">
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold">GitHub issues.</span> The primary channel for bug reports, design
          questions, and feature discussion. Search first, then <a
            href={FIPS_ISSUES}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-fips-accent underline">open a new one</a
          > if nothing matches.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold">Pull requests.</span> Walk the <a
            href={FIPS_CONTRIBUTING}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-fips-accent underline">CONTRIBUTING</a
          > guide, keep commits focused, and update the relevant spec in the same change when you touch
          wire format, routing, or configuration behaviour.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold">Nostr.</span> FIPS is a Nostr-native project. The author and a growing
          crowd of FIPS tinkerers hang out there and discuss new builds, test-node topology, and protocol
          quirks. The <a
            href={FIPS_HASHTAG_URL}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-fips-accent underline"><code class="font-mono">#FIPS</code> hashtag feed</a
          > on ants.sh is the easiest way to follow along, and the <a
            href={FIPS_ANNOUNCEMENT_URL}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="text-fips-accent underline">original announcement note</a
          > is a good thread to reply under.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-semibold">The mesh itself.</span> Once you are on the test mesh from the previous
          lesson, <code class="font-mono">fipsctl show peers</code> shows you who else is online. A short
          <code class="font-mono">ssh -6</code> or a Nostr DM to one of them is a perfectly fine way to
          say hi.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">What a useful bug report looks like</h2>

      <p>
        The protocol still changes. A good report keeps the feedback loop tight and saves everyone a
        round trip:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-fips-muted text-sm">
        <li>
          FIPS version (<code class="font-mono">fipsctl show status</code>), Rust version, OS,
          transport you are using.
        </li>
        <li>What you did, what you expected, what happened.</li>
        <li>
          Relevant output from <code class="font-mono">fipsctl show links</code>,
          <code class="font-mono">show tree</code>, <code class="font-mono">show mmp</code>, or the
          <code class="font-mono">fips</code> log, trimmed to the interesting window.
        </li>
        <li>
          If the bug touches routing or coordinates, the pair of npubs involved and whether the link
          was freshly established.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Ways to help, in order of effort</h2>

      <div class="space-y-3 not-prose my-2">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30">
          <p class="font-semibold text-fips-accent text-sm mb-1">Run a node</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-fips-muted">
            Every node you keep online is a new peer someone else can reach. If it stays up for more
            than a day, add it to your bootstrap config so friends can pin you too.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30">
          <p class="font-semibold text-fips-accent text-sm mb-1">
            Read a spec and file what you find
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-fips-muted">
            The design docs are the ground truth. If a paragraph is unclear, under-specified, or
            contradicts the code, that is a bug worth reporting. This site was written from them, so
            ambiguities surfaced here are worth fixing upstream.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30">
          <p class="font-semibold text-fips-accent text-sm mb-1">Ship a small patch</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-fips-muted">
            Transport fixes, clippy warnings, docs, an added <a
              href={FIPS_TESTING}
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="text-fips-accent underline">integration harness</a
            > case. Small PRs get merged fast and teach you the codebase.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30">
          <p class="font-semibold text-fips-accent text-sm mb-1">
            Bring an application onto the mesh
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-fips-muted">
            Anything that speaks IPv6 works unmodified. The Nostr relay, Kubernetes, and WireGuard
            examples in the repo are good starting points. Your own sidecar is the best way to
            pressure-test the IPv6 adapter.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30">
          <p class="font-semibold text-fips-accent text-sm mb-1">Improve this site</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-fips-muted">
            Spot an inaccuracy, a confusing diagram, or a missing lesson? <a
              href={LEARN_FIPS_REPO}
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener"
              class="text-fips-accent underline">learn-fips</a
            > is MIT-licensed and happy to take PRs. The lessons data drives the navigation, so adding
            a new lesson is a couple of files.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Hear it from the source</h2>

      <p>
        If you want the project's own words on why FIPS exists and where it is headed, these are the
        two most concentrated doses:
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-3 not-prose my-2">
        <a
          href={FIPS_ANNOUNCEMENT_URL}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30 hover:border-fips-accent/40 transition-colors block"
        >
          <div class="font-semibold text-fips-accent mb-1">Announcing FIPS</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-fips-muted">
            Johnathan Corgan's v0.1.0 announcement on Nostr. The pitch in his own words: Nostr gives
            you identity, FIPS gives you the network underneath.
          </div>
        </a>
        <a
          href={SOVENG_PODCAST_URL}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="rounded-lg border border-fips-border p-4 bg-fips-surface/30 hover:border-fips-accent/40 transition-colors block"
        >
          <div class="font-semibold text-fips-accent mb-1">No Solutions #24</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-fips-muted">
            36-minute walk through how FIPS started, what 150 nodes on the testnet taught them, and
            where the protocol is going next.
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">A closing note</h2>

      <p>
        Networks are social objects before they are technical ones. FIPS only exists because people
        keep showing up, running nodes, and arguing about the right way to encode an error signal.
        Read the source, say hi, break something useful. That is the whole job.
      </p>
    </section>

    <LessonNav current={14} />
  </article>

  <section class="hex-bg relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="hero-mesh-wrap absolute inset-0">
      <HeroMesh client:load />
      <div class="hero-mesh-fade absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none"></div>
    </div>
    <figure class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 pt-16 pb-40 md:pb-48">
      <span
        aria-hidden="true"
        class="absolute -top-2 left-4 md:left-6 text-fips-accent font-mono text-6xl leading-none select-none"
        >&ldquo;</span
      >
      <blockquote class="text-fips-text text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed italic">
        <p class="mb-4">
          Engineering solutions to problems is mostly about assembling existing pieces into a new
          whole, more so than inventing a new wheel.
        </p>
        <p>
          FIPS combines known, battle tested concepts going back decades in the fields of
          networking, cryptography, distributed computing, resilient communications, and operating
          systems, with full credit to those who came before.
        </p>
      </blockquote>
      <figcaption class="mt-6 text-sm text-fips-muted font-mono">
        &mdash;
        <a
          href={CORGAN_QUOTE_URL}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="text-fips-accent hover:underline">Johnathan Corgan</a
        >, author of FIPS
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>
</Base>
